<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top: 12pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; background-color: #ffffff;">ITEM 2.02. RESULTS OF OPERATIONS AND
FINANCIAL CONDITION</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">Representatives of SunTrust Banks, Inc.
(the "Registrant") are scheduled to make a
presentation to analysts at the Banc of America Securities 34th Annual
Investment Conference on Monday, September 20, 2004 at 4:30 p.m.
Eastern Time. A copy of the slide package used by the Registrant at
this conference is being furnished as Exhibit 99.1 to this Current
Report on Form 8-K and is incorporated by reference in this Item 2.02.
Such slide package also will be available on the Registrant's Web
site at <u>www.suntrust.com</u>. Information contained on the
Registrant's website is expressly not incorporated by reference
into this Current Report on Form 8-K.</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">The information in the
preceding paragraph, as well as Exhibit 99.1 referenced therein, shall
not be deemed "filed" for purposes of Section
18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, nor shall it be deemed
incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of
1933.</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top: 12pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; background-color: #ffffff;">ITEM 9.01.         (1)

      <P
       STYLE="border: solid 0 white;position:absolute;top:433px;left:123.375px;height:50.75px;width:565.5px; text-align:left;line-height:8px;padding: 0in 0in 0in 0in;">
        <FONT
         STYLE="border: solid 0 white;font-family:Arial;font-size:4.2pt;">SunTrust
        presents a return on average realized shareholders&#146; equity, as well as a
        return on average assets less net unrealized securities gains. These two ratios
        <BR>reflect primarily adjustments to remove the effects of the Company&#146;s
        securities portfolio which includes the ownership by the Company of 48.3
        million shares of The <BR>Coca-Cola Company. The Company uses this information
        internally to gauge its actual performance in the industry. SunTrust believes
        that the return on assets <BR>less the net unrealized securities gains is more
        indicative of the Company&#146;s return on assets because it fully reflects the
        return on assets that are related to the <BR>Company&#146;s core businesses,
        which are primarily customer relationship and customer transaction driven. The
        Company also believes that the return on average <BR>realized equity is more
        indicative of the Company&#146;s return on equity because the excluded equity
        relates primarily to a long term holding of a specific security. See <BR>the
        reconciliations slides in the appendix. </FONT>
      </P>
